;p>The idea is simple. Sequential UUIDv4 (128 bit) consists of &lt;code>unix timestamp (32 bit) + random bytes (96 bit)&lt;/code>&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>File Downloading in Headless Chrome Using ChromeDriver and Hound</title><link>https://fahri.id/posts/file-downloading-in-headless-chrome-using-chromedriver-and-hound/</link><pubDate>Mon, 16 Sep 2019 13:10:45 +0700</pubDate><author><name>Fahri</name></author><guid>https://fahri.id/posts/file-downloading-in-headless-chrome-using-chromedriver-and-hound/</guid><description><![CDATA[<p>Recently, I am making a simple Elixir application performing some actions to a website in an automated way.</p>
